  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 27-35.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - FINAL DESCENT OF MOSES FROM SINAI. The covenant having been renewed, Moses prepared to descend, having first however received a command to commit to writing the words of this second covenant (ver. 27). He received back the tables from God, inscribed with the Ten Commandments, and after a stay in Sinai of equal duration with the former one (ver. 28), descended, having the tables in his hands. He was not aware that the skin of his face had become radiant (ver. 29), and first learnt the fact by the rulers being afraid to come near him (ver. 30). After conversing with them and with the people he resolved to \"put a vail on his face\" ordinarily, only taking it of[ when he \"went in before the Lord\" into the ,, tent of meeting,\" and when, having received a message from the Lord to the people, he came out to deliver it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 27.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Write thou these words",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Literally, \"write ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "thee",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " these words\" - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", \"write them for thyself and for thy people.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "According to the tenor of these words have I made a covenant",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". That is, \"the covenant on my part is conditional on the observance of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "these words",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " on the part of Israel.\" The \"words\" intended are those of vers. 10-26. Exodus 34:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
